MINNA – Armed bandits in their numbers Saturday evening invaded the Gwada community in Shiroro Local Government Area while the Muslim faithful were breaking their fifteenth Ramadan fast, killing a police officer and three civilians. The invaders who were said to have entered Gwada village through a bush path linking the area and Kaduna village also abducted a number of persons, including women and their children. Eye witness account told our correspondent that the armed men started shooting sporadically into the air to scare away possible intruders as they headed to the homes of their victims and took them along with them. The Police Public Relation Officer (PPRO), Niger state command, Wasiu A Abiodun, confirmed the attack. Wasiu in a statement yesterday said, “The police responded immediately by drafting combined force of police tactical team and other security agencies with vigilante were mobilized to the area and repelled the hoodlums”.  The PPRO who however told journalists that details of the number of persons abducted were still sketchy as at the time of this report said, so far reinforcement has been dispatched to Gwada and normalcy has been restored.